SUMMARY:Oaks Bottom Refuge - Evening Run
DESCRIPTION:Portland Trail Runners\n**Join us for an evening run at** **Oaks Bottom Refuge****! We’ll meet at** **SE 6th and Tacoma** **and head out along the** **Springwater Corridor** **before turning onto** **South Meadow Trail** **and climbing up to the** **Bluff Trail****. From there\, we’ll take a left onto** **North Woodland Trail****\, loop back down to the Springwater\, and enjoy an out-and-back for a total of about** **6 miles****.**\n\n**Expect a mix of flat\, smooth paths and some rolling trail/climb sections\, plus views of the wetlands and the Willamette. (Both trail and paved)**\n\n***Note: both paved and dirt trails on this run\; remember your*** ***HEADLAMPS*** **🌟**\n\n**The route**\n[All Trails](https://www.alltrails.com/explore/map/oaks-bottom-refuge-se-run-811647f?u=i&sh=5spen7)\n\n***Want a shorter option?*** **Follow the route above\, and turn back around at where Bluff Trail meets North Woodland for** **3.6 miles****.**\n\n**Where to meet**\n**We’ll meet at SE Sixth and Tacoma.**\n**⏱️** ***We start running at 6:37pm!***\n\n**What to bring**\n\n* **Headlamps**\n\n**After the run**\n**Group kudos and home!**
